The office of the premier of Free State has given a detailed plan on how Premier Sisi Ntombela plans to implement the findings of Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane on her investigation into the Vrede dairy project, as she was ordered by Mkhwebane. Mkhwebane, in her report, gave the premier 30 days to report to her office what steps the premier would be taking in order to discipline those who are implicated in corruption and maladministration in her report titled: “Allegations of maladministration against the Free State Department of Agriculture – Vrede Integrated Dairy Project”. The premier’s spokesperson Tiisetso Makhele said the provincial government would continue to cooperate with all law enforcement agencies on investigations relating to the dairy farm and any other investigation. “It is in the interest of the Free State provincial government that this matter is brought to its finality,” Makhele said. -TNA Reporter